#Approach:

Approach (Recursive – Backtracking):

Is question me number linked list me diya hai.
Hume usme +1 add karna hai.

Important observation:
Addition hamesha last digit se start hoti hai.
But singly linked list me last pe direct ja nahi sakte.
Isliye recursion use karte hain.

Step 1:
Recursion ko last node tak bhejo.

Step 2:
Last node pe +1 add karo.

Step 3:
Agar value 10 ho jaye → node = 0, carry = 1
Else carry = 0

Step 4:
Carry ko previous nodes me propagate karo.

Step 5:
Agar sab nodes 9 the (like 9→9→9),
to new head bana do with value 1.

Example:
1 → 2 → 9
Recursion:
9 + 1 = 10 → 0 carry 1
2 + 1 = 3
1 → 3 → 0

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n) recursion stack

#Code:

/*Definition of singly linked list:
class ListNode {
    int val;
    ListNode next;

    ListNode() {
        val = 0;
        next = null;
    }

    ListNode(int data1) {
        val = data1;
        next = null;
    }

    ListNode(int data1, ListNode next1) {
        val = data1;
        next = next1;
    }
}
 */

class Solution {

    private int helper(ListNode head){
        ListNode temp = head;
        //base case
        if(temp == null){
            return 1;
        }

        int carry = helper(temp.next);
        temp.val = temp.val + carry;
        if(temp.val < 10){
            return 0;
        }
        temp.val = 0;
        return 1;
    }

    public ListNode addOne(ListNode head) {

        int carry = helper(head);
        if(carry == 1){
            ListNode newNode = new ListNode(1);
            newNode.next = head;
            return newNode;
        }
        return head;
    }
}
